<TITLE> Govt will make more arrests over corruption soon: Matin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 31 (bdnews24.com) - Communications adviser MA Matin Thursday said more politicians, businessmen and bureaucrats would be arrested for corruption, without publication of any list. The anticorruption taskforce would also probe corruption in private organisations, the former army officer told reporters. He had a meeting on the progress in implementation of projects included in the annual development programme (ADP) at the Rail Bhaban. Matin said there were specific allegations against the 12 people arrested since midnight Monday, which the taskforce was looking into. He added that action would be taken in line with the law and that anybody facing allegation of corruption would be arrested. The adviser said that politicians, businessmen and government officials had laundered huge amounts of money abroad. Of the amount, Tk 367 crore has been brought back voluntarily by the people who had sent the money abroad. The government was also trying to bring back the money siphoned off by the 12 latest arrestees, he said. The taskforce would now probe corruption in autonomous and private organisations alongside that in public ones, Matin said. He said that without any listing, more politicians, businessmen and bureaucrats would be arrested on charges of corruption. The Anticorruption Commission had submitted 19 FIRs and of them, charges had been pressed against eight. Three persons had been brought to justice and punished, Matin said. Currently, 24 allegations were being investigated and five of them were at the advanced stages, he said. bdnews24.
